{
  "stem": "2590.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in 1939, the foreign minister from Russia, Molotov, and the foreign minister from Germany, Ribbentrop, signed a pact of non-aggression.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they divided Poland into two parts.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Eastern part of Poland, where I was born, where I lived, became Russia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Western part the Germans took over.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Well, then an evil story started.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Somehow, the Russians considered us bourgeois, even we were not.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My uncle was rich, but we were just middle class people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And right away, the [NON-ENGLISH]-- that's like the CIA here-- took over our house and we had to move in to the grandparents.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they took over the grandparents' house, and we wandered like gypsies.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But my sister and I did attend school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then, we received the passport number 11, which meant that we are not good element for communist Russia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we had to move to Ostrog.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Ostrog was closer to the Russian border.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And, in a few months, we had to be sent to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "My mother and my father had to go to court.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And my mother spoke fluently Russian.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "She graduated gymnasium in Odessa.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And she was an intelligent woman.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "She made a very good impression on the judge.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And the judge said, no, a woman with your talent, with your quality, with your knowledge of the language and your outlook at life should not be wasted in Siberia.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they sent us back to our city, where we rented an apartment and we lived until 1941. 1941, September, the Germans came.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And really, fear and panic struck the whole Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "As soon as the Germans came, the city, especially the Jewish quarter, were bombarded day and night.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And myself, and the whole family, we ran to a cemetery where we spent two days.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
